There are glances that tell more than words without making any noise. They penetrate without knocking in your head, whispering stories that the soul devours. They are able to show emotions running between two beats of the heart. They can vomit all the evil that their lips can not let out. They are infinite, like the sea, and you are a pirate who doesn't know where to land. There are no boundaries, or streets, just willing to convey without thinking. These looks cannot be scared because they had a tough life. There are no rules or objections, in any case they will slam the truth raw and naked into your face. They follow the instinct, they do not need maps or navigators, they just come in. They choose few among many, crossing their destinies they trace lines parallel to horizons. In front of these looks, you just have to give up and let you carried away by the currents.

The heart has the size of a closed fist and a shape similar to a pear with the tip pointing down. The heart is the organ symbol of love, it follows the rhythm of emotions. Normally in an adult the heart contracts 60-70 times per minute; in a person in love many more, sometimes you get to 100 without realizing it. It almost seems that the irrepressible flow of time when we are close is directly proportional to the amount of beats you make to my heart in your presence. When your heart beats strong for another person you are no longer the one in control. .

When I was young:
I would restart the videogame every time I knew I was going to lose. I would sleep with all my plush animals so none of them got angry. I had that 4-color pen, and I would try to push all the buttons at once. I would wait behind a door to frighten someone, then I went away because they had taken too long to go out or I had to pee. I would pretend to sleep, so I could be carried to bed. I would think the moon followed my car. I would watch two drops of water slipping on the window, pretending it was a race.
Every time I Ingested fruit trees I was scared to death that a tree would grow in my belly. My knees were always scraped but they healed better than a broken heart. I remember when we were kids and could not wait to grow.
What the hell we were thinking?
